 0602: static struct _cydecimal _add_decimals(struct _cydecimal first, struct _cydecimal second) {
 0603:     iterable_t i;
 0604:         iterable_t  dig2 = _n_whole_digits(&second);
 0605:     iterable_t dig1 = _n_whole_digits(&first);
 0606:     // NOTE : TODO : revamp this system to also account for the length of digits - with _subtract_decimals too
 0607:     const bool dig1_b = ((dig1 >= MAX_INDICE) && (abs(first.exp) >= abs(MAX_INDICE-dig1)));
 0608:     const bool dig2_b = ((dig2 >= MAX_INDICE) && (abs(second.exp) >= abs(MAX_INDICE-dig2)));
 0609:     const exponent_t to_move = (abs(abs(first.exp)-abs(second.exp)));
 0610:     
 0611:     if (dig1_b || dig2_b){
 0612:         if (dig1_b && dig2_b){
 0613:             _round_decimal(&first, 1);
 0614:             _round_decimal(&second, 1);
 0615:         }
 0616:         else if (dig1_b){
 0617:             i=to_move;
 0618:             if (i > (dig1-dig2)) i=(dig1-dig2);
 0619:             _left_shift_digits(&second, (i)/2); // make the second one left shifted and the first one right shifted halfway
 0620:             _right_shift_digits(&first, (i)/2);
 0621:         }
 0622:         else{ // second is too large
 0623:             i=to_move;
 0624:             if (i > (dig2-dig1)) i=(dig2-dig1);
 0625:             _left_shift_digits(&first, (i)/2); // make the second one left shifted and the first one right shifted halfway
 0626:             _right_shift_digits(&second, (i)/2);
 0627:         } // this function should handle very large cases
 0628:     }
 0629:     if ((first.exp > second.exp)) {
 0630:         _left_shift_digits(&first, (first.exp - second.exp)); // trying to make first less - closer to second i.e minimize exp
 0631:     } else if (second.exp > first.exp) {
 0632:         _left_shift_digits(&second, second.exp - first.exp);
 0633:     }
 0634:     if (first.negative ^ second.negative){  // if either one is negative, essentially subtraction
 0635:         if (second.negative){
 0636:             _negate(&second);
 0637:             return _subtract_decimals(first, second);
 0638:         }
 0639:         else{
 0640:             _negate(&first);
 0641:             first = _subtract_decimals(first, second);
 0642:             _negate(&first);
 0643:             return first;
 0644:         }
 0645:     }
 0646:     else if (first.negative && second.negative){  // both are negative, add their absolute and returns its negative.
 0647: 
 0648:         first = _abs_dec(first);
 0649:         second = _abs_dec(second);
 0650: 
 0651:         first = (_add_decimals(first, second));
 0652:         _negate(&first);
 0653:         return first;
 0654:     }
 0655: 
 0656:     char overflow = 0, res = 0, z, y;
 0657:     
 0658:     for (i = MAX_LENGTH; i > 0; i--) {
 0659:         y = second.digits[i-1];
 0660:         z = first.digits[i-1];
 0661: 
 0662:         if ((overflow != 0) || ((z!=0) || (y!=0))) {
 0663:             res = z + y + overflow;
 0664:             overflow = res;
 0665: 
 0666:             if (overflow > 9) {
 0667:                 overflow = overflow % 10;
 0668:             }
 0669: 
 0670:             first.digits[i-1] = overflow;
 0671:             overflow = (char)((res - overflow) * 0.1);
 0672:         }
 0673:     }
 0674:     // const char r = _close_zero(&first);
 0675:     // if (r==1){
 0676:     //     return _empty_decimal();
 0677:     // }
 0678:     // else if(r==0){
 0679:     //     _round_decimal(&first, 2);
 0680:     // }
 0681:     return first;
 0682: }

 0977:                     if y > 9:  # overflow lmao
 0978:                         y = -y
 0979: 
 0980:                 if y == 0 and overflow == 0:
 0981:                     continue
 0982:

 0985:                     result.digits[j-place_val] = overflow % 10

 0987:                 else:
 0988:                     result.digits[j-place_val] = overflow
 0989:                     overflow=0
 0990: 
 0991:         postincrement(place_val)
 0992:             # This line adds the carry-over to the next digit
 0993: 
 0994:     if negate:

 0996:             if result.digits[i] != 0:
 0997:                 result.digits[i] = -result.digits[i]

 0999:     _normalize_digits(&result, False)
